paragraphs.title: Calculate Quantiles by group
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
from pyspark.sql.types import *
import numpy as np
import pyspark.sql.functions as fn

#####
def extract_quantile_bygroup_value (num_varname,cat_varname,cat_varname_value,my_dataframe,my_quantiles):
    #num_varname = name of the numerical variable for which we compute quantiles
    #cat_varname = name of the categorical variable to use in by group
    #cat_varname_value = specific value of the categorical variable cat_varname
    #my_dataframe = dataframe containing both numeric and categorical variables
    #my_quantiles = list of quantiles to calculate
    
    #For log purposes
    print "Executing: extract_quantile_bygroup_value"
    
    #.filter() statement if value of cat_varname is null 
    if cat_varname_value is None:
        filter_string=cat_varname+" is null"
    #.filter() statement if value of cat_varname is not null
    else:
        filter_string=cat_varname+"=='%s'" %cat_varname_value

    #compute the quantiles of num_varname
    qt_computed=my_dataframe.filter("%s" %filter_string).approxQuantile("%s" %num_varname,my_quantiles,0.0)
    
    #return quantile/s
    return qt_computed
    
#####
def quantile_bygroup_dictionary (num_varname,cat_varname,my_dataframe,my_quantiles):
    #num_varname = name of the numerical variable for which we compute quantiles
    #cat_varname = name of the categorical variable to use in by group
    #my_dataframe = dataframe containing both numeric and categorical variables
    #my_quantiles = list of quantiles to calculate
    
    #For log purposes
    print "Executing: quantile_bygroup_dictionary"
    
    #initialize dictionary collecting the quantile results
    qt_collect = {}
    
    #create list of values of the categorical variable cat_varname
    list_values=my_dataframe.rdd.map(lambda x: x[cat_varname]).distinct().collect()

    #cycle through the list of values of cat_varname and compute quantiles for each of them
    for value in list_values:
        #print cat_varname,"=='%s'"  %value #just to show the progress of execution
        key_string=cat_varname+"_%s" %value #create key value for qt_collect dictionary (name of categorical variable + _ + value)
        #collect computed quantiles as dictionary elements 
        qt_collect["%s"  %key_string]= extract_quantile_bygroup_value (num_varname,cat_varname,value,my_dataframe,my_quantiles)
    
    #return dictionary 
    return qt_collect
    

#####
def quantile_bygroup_dataframe (num_varname,cat_varname,my_dataframe,my_quantiles):
    #num_varname = name of the numerical variable for which we compute quantiles
    #cat_varname = name of the categorical variable to use in by group
    #my_dataframe = dataframe containing both numeric and categorical variables
    #my_quantiles = list of quantiles to calculate
    
    #For log purposes
    print "Executing: quantile_bygroup_dataframe"
    
    #create list of values of the categorical variable cat_varname
    list_values=my_dataframe.rdd.map(lambda x: x[cat_varname]).distinct().collect()
    
    #calculate by group quantile/s and return them as dictionary
    qt_dictionary=quantile_bygroup_dictionary(num_varname,cat_varname,my_dataframe,my_quantiles)
    
    #create schema (metadata) for the data frame that will contain the by group quantile/s
    dataframe_field = [StructField("quantile",StringType(),True),StructField("%s" %num_varname,StringType(),True),StructField("%s" %cat_varname, StringType(), True)]
    dataframe_schema = StructType(dataframe_field)
    collect_df = sqlContext.createDataFrame(sc.emptyRDD(), dataframe_schema)
    
    #cycle through the list of values of cat_varname to cast the dictionary into a dataframe
    for value in list_values:
        #print cat_varname,"=='%s'"  %value #just to show the progress of execution
        key_string=cat_varname+"_%s" %value
        temp = zip(my_quantiles, qt_dictionary["%s"  %key_string])
        temp_dataframe = sqlContext.createDataFrame(temp,['quantile','%s' %num_varname]).withColumn("%s"  %cat_varname,fn.lit("%s" %value))
        collect_df=collect_df.unionAll(temp_dataframe)
    
    #retrun dataframe    
    return collect_df
    
#create list of quantiles to calculate in float format (arange creates numpy.float64 format which is not compatible with pyspark) --START
qt_list=list(np.arange(0,1,0.01))
for index, item in enumerate(qt_list):
    qt_list[index] = float(item)
#create list of quantiles to calculate in float format (arange creates numpy.float64 format which is not compatible with pyspark) --END

#calculate quantiles for n transactions by mpog_flag_discontinued_flag_stocking_location
quantile_data_artificial=quantile_bygroup_dataframe ("value","class",data_artificial,qt_list)
